We got to the bar around 10pm last night and the place was fairly empty. We placed our coats on one of several open tables and went to the bar to order drinks because no one came to serve us. After we received the drinks the rudest server I ever encounter came yelling at us that if we didn’t buy drinks from her that we needed to remove our jackets. She then proceeded to say that if we didn’t remove our jackets that she was going to throw them in the lost and found. We told her we would of happily bought drinks from her but when we arrived she was no where to be seen. She became even more irate and went to security to kick us out. Security couldn’t of been any nicer and basically hinted to us that she’s rude like this all the time. We then proceeded to have to go to the bar the whole night because she wouldn’t serve us. We were one of the few customers in there...you would think we could of had better service.  When I asked what her name was she rolled her eyes and walked away but she had short brown hair and purple lipstick on last night. I will never go back based on the extremely rude and uncalled attitude from the server. She clearly had some anger issues and should not be a server.

On August 17th, I reserved a table for a party of 7 for my brother’s birthday. Everything was going good, my waitress Bailey was GREAT. The problem came as my party and I were getting ready to leave. Noticing that we had a bit of mimosa to drink after we paid for our food, I had my brother chug his so we could go to our next destination. Very abruptly, a staff member comes over and says to me that he can’t do that. We ignored him. The same staff member comes back no more than 5 minutes later and snatches my glass out my hand mid-pour and starts making a scene. He’s talking over me, getting louder and louder and calls security over to kick us out.... even though we were leaving ANYWAY. Needless to say, despite my server being great, I will NEVER step foot into this establishment again because what I won’t tolerate is rude, belligerent behavior. That staff member invaded my personal space, and almost ruined my brother’s birthday. I would honestly like to speak to the owners because I question the integrity of a place that allows its staff to treat paying customers with such blatant disrespect. Don’t go here. Its not worth rude behavior.

There are a few places in Chicago with "club brunch" events, and Benchmark is one of them. Fremont is another in which they usually have a live DJ and/or dance floor along with brunch stations. You pay a flat fee and get bottomless mimosas and all you can eat breakfast. If you're up for day drinking, club music, and have a larger crowd of friends, this can be a great time.  I personally prefer brunch with a single date or a small group and a chill atmosphere, so the Benchmark isn't really for me, but I can definitely see the appeal. 20 minutes south of this location is the Fremont.

I wish I could give them 10 stars! Absolutely great place and top-level customer service. Staff is friendly and accommodating. I went there on Thursday night for the first time. The restaurant has a sports bar feel, however also has seating outside and looks like it has the potential to have a day party vibe as well. I got there and was seated with my friends. I ordered the nachos but somehow the nice waitress heard tacos which is understandable with the setting having music playing as well as TVs going I the background and chatter from neighboring tables. The food came quick, although the wrong order. She called the owner (I think) Billy, who was an absolute sweetheart, and he clarified my order with me a few times and was very apologetic and said he would let the cook know. Needless to say, shortly after he did not only bring me a plate of nachos, but a whole tray that could LITERALLY feed our whole table of 8 twice. He once again apologized and even came to follow up and ask if everything was all right and to my liking. When getting ready to pay, he expressed that my meal was on the house. I was in shock by how nice everyone was and so accommodating. They went above and beyond to rectify a small mistake and it made a lasting impression. I was very appreciative and I will most definitely be going back!
